properties.headline: Wind Advisory issued January 15 at 6:57PM PST until January 17 at 1:00AM PST by NWS Los Angeles/Oxnard CA
properties.description:
* WHAT...Southwest winds 20 to 35 mph with gusts up to 50 mph
expected. Strongest winds in the foothills.

* WHERE...Antelope Valley.

* WHEN...From 1 PM Thursday to 1 AM PST Friday.

* IMPACTS...Gusty winds could blow around unsecured objects. Tree
limbs could be blown down. Blowing dust could locally reduce
visibility in the desert at times Thursday afternoon in advance
of the rain.

* ADDITIONAL DETAILS...Travel may become hazardous for high
profile vehicles traveling along Highways 14 and 138 in the
Antelope Valley.
properties.instruction:
Use extra caution when driving, especially if operating a high
profile vehicle. Secure outdoor objects.

NWSheadline: WIND ADVISORY IN EFFECT FROM 1 PM THURSDAY TO 1 AM PST FRIDAY
